  Adaon smiles brightly.  "Aha, >music<!  Now ye are askin' some 
sensible questions.  A bard's >music< be his life, his very soul.  Take 
thot away, and he be little more than a two-bit street-corner fool.
  ">Bards< are the masters of the musical arts.  With the >lute< we 
craft sound, j'st as others may craft wagons, or horseshoes, or crystal 
goblets.  Wi' our merry tunes we can influence those around us, for 
nothing stirs the heart quite so much as a moving melody.  
Sometimes they feel stirred enough to reward us for our efforts, and 
justly so.  We put alot of effort and training int' our >music<.  >Music< 
also tames the savage beast.  I know this for a fact; it's saved me life 
on many an occasion.
  "If ye only want a single note, try >play lute C4<, or any other note
between C4 and C6 that yuir lute knows."
  "O' course, there be many other tricks o' the trade that y'll discover 
for y'rsel' if ye decide to join the >bards<."
